    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-10-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Lord <persName
                            type="to">Lyons</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 19, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt
                    of your note of the 11th instant, accompanied by a copy of a memorial addressed
                    to her Majesty’s principal secretary of state for foreign affairs, by Mr.
                    William Gray, owner of the British ship Perthshire, alleged to have been
                    interfered with by United States ships-of-war.</p>
                <p>A copy of those papers has been transmitted to the Secretary of the Navy with a
                    view to a proper investigation of the matter. When the reply of that officer
                    shall have been received, I shall lose no time in communicating to your lordship
                    the result of the investigation.</p>
                <p>Accept, my lord, the assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>The Right Hon. Lord <hi rend="smallcaps">Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
